@node "whatitis" "whatitis"
WHAT IS IT?

It's a small utility to give you random ORGANIZATION strings in a TCP/IP
setup.  Pointless but fun.
@endnode

@node "why" "Why?"
WHY?

I was bored and needed an orgasm :)
@endnode

@node "howdoidoit" "How do I do it?"
HOW DO I DO IT?

It is dead easy. 

Copy the executable to somewhere in your path, then set the two environment
variables as follows -

     SetEnv EDITOR   Orgasm
     SetEnv ORGASMED your_favourite_editor

If you have setup Orgasm correctly, it will happily do its thing over and over
again.  Multiple orgasms if you like.

Generating ORGANIZATION files is just as simple.  All you do is open a Shell
and type Orgasm.  Your editor will be started with the next new file.
@endnode

@node "limitations" "Limitations..."
LIMITATIONS

Not many really, but you will need a $ORGASMED environment variable. You'll be
told if it doesn't exist.
@endnode

@node "systemrequirements" "System Requirements..."
SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS

It was written on a 3.1 A4000/40 with 2 meg chip, 16 meg fast and no free
slots.  It should run on any 2.0 machine, below that I don't know and I'm not
dismembering my Lorraine to find out!

Something that uses ORGANIZATION variables might be handy too.
@endnode

